  m_text: Welcome to the launchpad. To break free from Earth's gravity, your spacecraft
    must reach an "escape velocity" of over 25,000 mph (11.2 km/s). Because of this
    immense gravitational pull, over 85% of the rocket sitting in front of you is
    pure fuel. Adjust your speed slider, initiate the launch sequence, and prepare
    to leave Earth's physics behind to manipulate the cosmos.
